---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | HEART"
  description="Learn about HEART's mission, values, and student-led approach to community-centered health equity work at York University."
>
  <div class="page">
    <section class="page-header">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="page-title">About HEART</h1>
        <p class="page-intro">
          HEART (Health Equity Advocacy Response Team) is a student-led organization dedicated to advancing
          <strong> health equity</strong> by addressing systemic, social, and economic barriers that prevent individuals
          and communities from achieving optimal health.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cards cards-3">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Our Vision</h3>
            <p>A world where every individual—regardless of background—has equal opportunity to achieve optimal health.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Our Mission</h3>
            <p>Advocate, educate, and act in response to health inequities through community-centered initiatives.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>What is Health Equity?</h3>
            <p>Ensuring everyone has a fair and just opportunity to be as healthy as possible by removing barriers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="section-lead section-lead-spaced">
          <strong>Barriers we address:</strong> poverty, discrimination, access gaps, language barriers, educational gaps, and more.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="/join">Join HEART</a>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href="/events">View events</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-muted">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Our Values</h2>

        <div class="cards cards-2">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Equity</h3>
            <p>Fairness and justice in access to health resources, education, and care.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Inclusion</h3>
            <p>Respect for all identities, backgrounds, and lived experiences.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Integrity</h3>
            <p>Ethical, evidence-based action and responsible community partnerships.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Collaboration</h3>
            <p>Working with communities, not over them—listening first, acting with care.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section-title">How We Work</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">
          HEART focuses on community-centered work that is student-led, collaborative, and grounded in health equity.
          We aim to learn from communities, support existing efforts, and contribute where students can be useful.
        </p>

        <div class="cards cards-3">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Student-led</h3>
            <p>York University students help shape initiatives, outreach, and advocacy priorities.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Community-centered</h3>
            <p>We value listening, partnership, and responsive action over one-size-fits-all programming.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>Interdisciplinary</h3>
            <p>Students from different programs and lived experiences can contribute to equity-focused work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
